<div class="container-fluid">
<div class="well padding2">
  <h3> Rick Barry changed the game at the free throw line as well as in the locker room </h3>
  <ul> 
    <li>Rick Barry was one of the only players promoting the underhanded shot while at the free throw line </li> 
    <li> A career 89% free-throw shooter, his technique netted him 5.6 points per game on average</li>
    <li> He only improved his foul shooting prowess over time with his last 3 seasons in the NBA being his best at 92%, 95%, and 94% respectively </li>
    <li> Barry scored from more than just the stripe with a career average of 24.8 ppg </li>
  </ul>
</div>
</div>
